# Runway Project Conventions

## Project Overview

Runway is a "Time to First API Call" tool that generates Quick Start guides from OpenAPI specs.

## Directory Structure

```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router
│   ├── api/          # Route handlers
│   └── (routes)/     # Pages
├── components/       # React components
│   └── ui/           # shadcn/ui components
├── lib/              # Business logic
│   └── openapi/      # OpenAPI parsing utilities
└── types/            # TypeScript type definitions
```

## Component Guidelines

- Server Components by default
- Client Components only for interactivity
- Colocate component-specific logic
- Use shadcn/ui for UI primitives

## Naming Conventions

- Files: `kebab-case.tsx`
- Components: `PascalCase`
- Functions: `camelCase`
- Types: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`

## Data Flow

1. OpenAPI spec URL → Server Action/Route Handler
2. Parse + validate on server
3. Return minimal data to client
4. Generate snippets client-side (for instant feedback)

## No AI Hallucinations

- Only show real data from the OpenAPI spec
- Never generate fake endpoints or auth schemes
- Clear error messages when spec is invalid
